---
import DemoComponentCard from '../../../../components/DemoComponentCard.astro';

export const title = 'Toggle icon';
export const order = 500;
---
<p>By default the toggle icon appears at the <strong>trailing end</strong> of the header. Add <code>leading-toggle</code> to <code>&lt;wc-accordion&gt;</code> to move it to the leading start.</p>

<h3>Trailing (default)</h3>
<DemoComponentCard lang={"html"}>
  <wc-accordion>
    <wc-accordion-item open>
      <span slot="heading">Panel A</span>
      <p>The expand icon sits at the trailing end of the header row.</p>
    </wc-accordion-item>
    <wc-accordion-item>
      <span slot="heading">Panel B</span>
      <p>Content for panel B.</p>
    </wc-accordion-item>
  </wc-accordion>
</DemoComponentCard>

<h3>Leading</h3>
<DemoComponentCard lang={"html"}>
  <wc-accordion leading-toggle>
    <wc-accordion-item open>
      <span slot="heading">Panel A</span>
      <p>The expand icon sits at the leading start of the header row.</p>
    </wc-accordion-item>
    <wc-accordion-item>
      <span slot="heading">Panel B</span>
      <p>Content for panel B.</p>
    </wc-accordion-item>
  </wc-accordion>
</DemoComponentCard>

<h3>Hidden</h3>
<p>Set <code>hide-toggle</code> on <code>&lt;wc-accordion-item&gt;</code> to remove the indicator entirely. Useful when the expand interaction is implied by context.</p>

<DemoComponentCard lang={"html"}>
  <wc-accordion>
    <wc-accordion-item hide-toggle>
      <span slot="heading">No indicator</span>
      <p>Click the header to toggle — no icon is shown.</p>
    </wc-accordion-item>
    <wc-accordion-item hide-toggle>
      <span slot="heading">Another panel</span>
      <p>Useful inside navigation or filter lists.</p>
    </wc-accordion-item>
  </wc-accordion>
</DemoComponentCard>
